n men to hazard their fortunes, go long journeys halfway about the world, forget friendships, even lie, cheat, and steal, all for the gain of a book.\n\n- A.S.W.\n|\nThe opposite of love is not hate, its apathy, when you simply don't bother about that person!\n\n- Amish Tripathi, The Secret of the Nagas\n|\nMark it. No challenges, no success!\n\n- Israelmore Ayivor, Six Words Inspiration\n|\nThe least learned, for the most part, have been always most ready to write.\n\n- Roger\n|\nPut down everything that comes into your head and then you're a writer. But an author is one who can judge his own stuff's worth, without pity, and destroy most of it.', 1964)\n\n- Colette\n|\nIf you do not direct your path, the world will. Don't ever let anyone make you go where you do not want to be.\n\n- Toni\n|\nThe truth is not in the commercial media because the truth is a dagger pointed at its heart, which is its pocketbook.\n\n- George Seldes, Facts and Fascism\n|\nThe question is whether any civilization can wage relentless war on life without destroying itself, and without losing the right to be called civilized.\n\n- Rachel\n|\nWhat you think about is what you get. The more you think about something, the more it manifests in your life.\n\n- Avina\n|\nThe only instance where five purely-negative words have had a highly positive, motivational impact, are Winston Churchill's 'Never, Never, Never, Never Give-Up'.\n\n- Nabil\n|\nTakes long,Stings hard,Benefit's large.That's your experience in life. :)\n\n- Babu\n|\nBefore you believe in doubt; before you journey with doubt; before you go the way of doubt, first, go to faith with faith and seek permission from faith.\n\n- Ernest\n|\nSolomon had a good thing going. He asked for wisdom and he got it, riches, and power. I think I'm going to ask for wisdom too.\n\n- Jochebed\n|\nCould there be any doubt that the Jews would seek to harm the Son of God again, knowing that his body was now readily accessible in the form of defenseless crackers?\n\n- Sam Harris, The End of Faith: Religion, Terror, and the Future of Reason\n|\nLove, too, was just a question of time\n\n- Paulo Coelho, The Devil and Miss Prym\n|\nink marks the page/where you execute your will like a doe announcing an/ox-stern mate with a single, bleary blink.\n\n- Melissa Lee-Houghton, A Body Made of You\n|\nDon't spend time beating on a wall, hoping to transform it into a door.\n\n- Coco\n|\nI can win an argument on any topic, against any opponent. People know this, and steer clear of me at parties. Often, as a sign of their great respect, they don't even invite me.\n\n- Dave\n|\nLife is a journey, Frannie darling,' Feagan had once told me. 'Choose well those with whom you travel.'As always, I've followed Feagan's counsel.\n\n- Lorraine Heath, Surrender to the Devil\n|\nIf we don’t do anything to change the lives of our people and our country, we live a vain life\n\n- Sunday\n|\nUna Salus Victis Nullam Sperare Salutem - (Latin - written 19 BC)The only hope for the doomed, is no hope at all...\n\n- Virgil, The Aeneid\n|\nKita selalu jumpa orang baik-baik sewaktu mengembara, bukan sebab nasib kita baik. Tapi sebab Tuhan kasihan.\n\n- Azzah A.R., Nota Perempuan Backpacker\n|\nA man's plumbing is like his mind: simple, very few surprises. You ladies, on the other hand...well, God put a lot of thought in making you.\n\n- Khaled\n|\nTrue freedom is the ability to respond consciously, in the most beneficial way, to whatever life throws at you.\n\n- John\n|\nHe utilizesform for a striking lecture;young poets shiverinexperience,but thaw over their own work,fertilize magic.\n\n- Kristen\n|\nWhat you do teaches faster, and has a lasting impression, far beyond what you say.\n\n- T.F. Hodge, From Within I Rise: Spiritual Triumph Over Death and Conscious Encounters with 'The Divine Presence'\n|\nAbove all things physical, it is more important to be beautiful on the inside - to have a big hear and an open mind and a spectacular spleen.\n\n- Ellen DeGene